04589nmm a2200613Ia 9780520970052DE-B159720240328111612.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240328t20222022cau    fo  d z      eng d  a97805209700527 a10.1525/97805209700522doi  a(DE-B1597)627300  a(OCoLC)1303570042  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  acaucUS-CA 4aHQ798b.H34 2022 7aSOC0260002bisacsh04a305.242/20905223/eng/202203071 aHardie, Jessica Halliday, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aBest Laid Plans :bWomen Coming of Age in Uncertain Times /cJessica Halliday Hardie. 1aBerkeley, CA : bUniversity of California Press, c[2022] 4c©2022  a1 online resource (274 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tIllustrations -- tAcknowledgments -- tIntroduction -- tPart I. Reconsidering Aspirations -- t1. High School Girls’ Plans -- t2. Anticipating a Packaged Future -- t3. Hoping for a Repackaged Future -- tPart II. Traversing the Transition to Adulthood -- t4. Dreams Unfurled -- t5. On Track -- t6. Holding On -- t7. Navigating Rough Seas -- tConclusion: Beyond Planfulness -- tAppendix: Methodology -- tNotes -- tReferences -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aGiven the range of possibilities open to women today, what futures do adolescent girls dream of and pursue? And how do social class and race play into their trajectories? In asking young women about their aspirations in three areas—school, work, and family—Best Laid Plans demonstrates how future plans are framed by notions of gendered responsibilities and abilities. Through her examination of the lives of poor, working-class, and middle-class Black and White young women as they navigate the transition to adulthood, sociologist Jessica Halliday Hardie defines anew what it means for young women to come of age. In particular, Hardie shows how social capital, either possessed or lacked, is not simply a resource for planning for the future but a structure whose form and function varies by social class and race. As these inequalities persist into adulthood, high aspirations, social capital, and careful planning bolster some young women while hindering others. Drawing on qualitative data from a five-year period, Best Laid Plans makes the case for why we need to move beyond the individual appeal to “dream bigger” and “plan better” and toward systematic changes that will put young people’s aspirations within reach.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aComing of agexSocial aspectszUnited Statesy21st centuryvCase studies. 0aTeenage girlszUnited StatesxSocial conditionsy21st centuryvCase studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishz978311099455108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022z9783110994520oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076649340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520970052?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520970052423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520970052/original  a978-3-11-076649-3  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099455-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DSLb2022